rch’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":43,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":52,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":87,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Peter Brynhill was born about 1172, in Lancashire, England. She had at least 1 son with Peter Brynhill."},"et":{"about 1172–":"umbes 1172–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1172–Female":"1172–Surnud","about 1172":"umbes 1172","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1172–":"noin 1172–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1172–Female":"1172–Kuollut","about 1172":"noin 1172","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"about 1172–":"environ 1172–Décédée"